## Validator Hotfix Update
We are rolling out some hotfixes to the validator code to improve stability and fairness in scoring. Validators please update asap.

**Max Processing Time Enforcement:**
We identified some miners registering slow hotkeys (up to 200s of processing time) to manipulate the speed score calculation.
To address this, we are introducing a maximum processing time of 15 seconds.
    •    Any processing time above 15 seconds will now receive a speed score of 0.
    •    Instead of normalizing with the highest processing time observed, normalization will now be done against the minimum between max_time and the 15.0 seconds threshold.
This change also improves speed score stability across varying batch sizes.

**Unresponsive Hotkeys:**
During major updates, we noticed that some hotkeys were completely unresponsive to challenges and could remain active, living off their past scores for up to 72 hours.
From now on, any hotkey that timeouts will be treated as if it submitted an empty response, resulting in the appropriate penalties.

These updates aim to enhance the overall reliability and fairness of the validation process.
